Remarks. The cephalic chaetotaxy in this species is typical of the longicornis clade rather than the pale/grey clade. The postocular macrochaetae are paired rather than widely separated, and 2 + 2 posterior macrochaetae are present. Previously examined species of the pale/grey clade have the postocular chaetae well separated and lack the more posterior pair of posterior macrochaetae (
Felderhoff et al. 2010
).
